<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Welcome | URL Shortener</title>

    <style>
        * {
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            box-sizing: border-box;
        }

        body {
            font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;
            background: #f4f4f4;
            display: flex;
            justify-content: center;
            align-items: center;
            height: 100vh;
        }

        .container {
            width: 500px;
            background: white;
            padding: 40px;
            border-radius: 10px;
            box-shadow: 0 5px 15px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
            text-align: center;
        }

        h1 {
            color: #333;
            margin-bottom: 15px;
        }

        p {
            color: #666;
            margin-bottom: 30px;
            line-height: 1.5;
        }

        .btn {
            display: inline-block;
            margin: 10px;
            padding: 12px 20px;
            background: #007bff;
            color: white;
            text-decoration: none;
            border-radius: 5px;
            font-weight: bold;
        }

        .btn:hover {
            background: #0056b3;
        }

        .btn-secondary {
            background: #28a745;
        }

        .btn-secondary:hover {
            background: #1e7e34;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

<div class="container">

    <h1>🔗 Welcome to URL Shortener</h1>

    <p>
        Create short URLs, share them easily, and track the number of clicks
        on each link—all from one simple application.
    </p>

    <a href="/shortner" class="btn">Create Short URL</a>
    <a href="/url" class="btn btn-secondary">View All URLs</a>
    <br><br>
    <a href="/login" class="btn">Login</a>
    <a href="/signup" class="btn btn-secondary">Sign Up</a>

</div>

</body>
</html>